content:
Check with your administrator to make sure that you have access to the records you’re trying to report on. If you’re still not seeing any results in your report, try casting a wider net.

Show more than your own records by selecting Show | All accounts.
Expand your time frame filters by selecting All Time for Range, or select a broader custom range.
Choose field filter operators carefully. For example, use Account Owner contains James instead of equals.
Check your filter logic to ensure you're not excluding all data.

Limiting your report can improve performance, but make sure you're not filtering out the data you want. 

If your report includes an external object, the results may not reflect the full dataset due to callout limits while fetching external object data. If the report results in few or no rows, try customizing the report to obtain more relevant external object rows.
title: Troubleshooting Salesforce Reports
